Record Class Token

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
org.flag4j.io.parsing.Token
Record Components:
kind - The kind of this token.
details - The details of this token.
record Token(String kind, String details) extends Record
A token is the smallest distinct meaningful unit of data extracted from a string while parsing.

    • errorCheck

      protected void errorCheck(String k, String d)
      If a given tokens kind and details match k and d respectively then an error will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      k - token kind
      d - token details
      Throws:
      LinearAlgebraException - If !this.matches(k, d).

    • errorCheck

      protected void errorCheck(String k)
      If a given token does not match the provided kind then the program will halt.
      Parameters:
      k - token kind.
      Throws:
      LinearAlgebraException - If !this.kind.equals(k).
